The conductivity measured at RT for the Ce1−xCuxO2 (x = 0.0, 0.05, 0.1, 0.2, and 0.3) has been investigated first as a function of frequency and then as a function of the composition at a constant frequency value, i.e., 103 Hz. AC conductivity (σac) is a crucial electrical characteristic that controls how well a material conducts electricity when exposed to an electrical field [35, 36]. Furthermore, an increase in the concentration and mobility of ions leads to a conductivity increase [37]. The AC's frequency dependency conductivity (σac) is most often represented by the Jonscher relation [38].5σac=σω-σdc=Aωs\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
